# ── Required ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The private key the bot signs with. For anything beyond testnet, prefer an
# encrypted keystore over a raw key (see docs/getting-started.md).
PRIVATE_KEY=0x...

# ── Network ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# "testnet" (Shannon, chain 50312) or "mainnet" (chain 5031). Start on testnet.
NETWORK=testnet

# Optional RPC / API overrides. Sensible defaults per network are built in
# (see packages/core/src/config/networks.ts) — only set these to use your own.
# RPC_URL=
# REST_API_URL=
# WS_URL=

# ── Session keys (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# For split-key / operator trading: set PRIVATE_KEY to your HOT operator key and
# OWNER_ADDRESS to the fund wallet it trades on behalf of. Orders then route
# through placeOrderFor and the hot key can never withdraw funds. One-time setup:
# scripts/operator-setup.ts (run with the fund key). See docs/session-keys.md.
# OWNER_ADDRESS=0x...

# ── SIWE (HTTP API auth) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The Chain ID in the SIWE login message MUST match NETWORK: 5031 mainnet,
# 50312 testnet. The core sets this for you from NETWORK — do not override
# unless you know why (a mismatch is rejected). See docs/gotchas.md.

# ── Strategy knobs are in each strategy's own .env.example ───────────────────
